[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"This page provides detailed documentation for all public functions and types in Capse.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Core-Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Core Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#CℓEmulator","page":"API Reference","title":"CℓEmulator","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Capse.CℓEmulator","page":"API Reference","title":"Capse.CℓEmulator","text":"CℓEmulator(; TrainedEmulator, ℓgrid, InMinMax, OutMinMax, Postprocessing)\n\nMain struct for CMB angular power spectrum emulation.\n\nFields\n\nTrainedEmulator::AbstractTrainedEmulators: Trained neural network model\nℓgrid::AbstractVector: Multipole moments (ℓ values) on which the emulator was trained\nInMinMax::AbstractMatrix: Min-max normalization parameters for inputs (2×n_params)\nOutMinMax::AbstractMatrix: Min-max normalization parameters for outputs (2×n_ℓ)\nPostprocessing::Function: Post-processing function with signature f(input, output, emulator)\n\nExample\n\n# Typically created via load_emulator, but can be constructed manually:\nemulator = CℓEmulator(\n    TrainedEmulator = trained_nn,\n    ℓgrid = collect(2:2500),\n    InMinMax = [mins max_vals],  # 2×n_params matrix\n    OutMinMax = [mins max_vals],  # 2×n_ℓ matrix\n    Postprocessing = (input, output, emu) -> output\n)\n\nSee also: load_emulator, get_Cℓ\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"The main struct for CMB power spectrum emulation. Contains the trained neural network, normalization parameters, and post-processing functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Fields:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"TrainedEmulator::AbstractTrainedEmulators: The trained neural network model\nℓgrid::AbstractVector: Multipole moments (ℓ values) for the power spectrum\nInMinMax::AbstractMatrix: Min-max normalization parameters for inputs (2×n_params matrix)\nOutMinMax::AbstractMatrix: Min-max normalization parameters for outputs (2×n_ℓ matrix)\nPostprocessing::Function: Post-processing function applied to network output","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"# Manual construction (advanced users)\nCℓ_emu = Capse.CℓEmulator(\n    TrainedEmulator = trained_nn,\n    ℓgrid = [2, 3, 4, ..., 2500],\n    InMinMax = normalization_input,\n    OutMinMax = normalization_output,\n    Postprocessing = (input, output, emu) -> output\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Primary-Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Primary Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#get_Cℓ","page":"API Reference","title":"get_Cℓ","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Capse.get_Cℓ","page":"API Reference","title":"Capse.get_Cℓ","text":"get_Cℓ(input_params, Cℓemu::AbstractCℓEmulators) -> Vector{Float64} or Matrix{Float64}\n\nCompute CMB angular power spectrum C_ℓ for given cosmological parameters.\n\nArguments\n\ninput_params: Cosmological parameters\nVector{<:Real}: Single set of parameters (length must match emulator's expectation)\nMatrix{<:Real}: Multiple parameter sets (size nparams × nsamples)\nCℓemu::AbstractCℓEmulators: The emulator instance\n\nReturns\n\nVector{Float64}: Power spectrum values on the emulator's ℓ-grid (single evaluation)\nMatrix{Float64}: Power spectra where each column is one spectrum (batch evaluation)\n\nThrows\n\nArgumentError: If input dimensions don't match emulator requirements\nArgumentError: If input contains NaN or Inf values\nAssertionError: If parameter count doesn't match expected dimensions\n\nExamples\n\n# Single evaluation\nparams = [0.02237, 0.1200, 0.6736, 0.9649, 0.0544, 2.042e-9]\nCℓ = get_Cℓ(params, emulator)\n\n# Batch evaluation (100 cosmologies)\nparams_batch = rand(6, 100)\nCℓ_batch = get_Cℓ(params_batch, emulator)\n\n# Access specific multipole\nℓ_grid = get_ℓgrid(emulator)\nidx_ℓ100 = findfirst(==(100), ℓ_grid)\nCℓ_at_100 = Cℓ[idx_ℓ100]\n\nSee also: load_emulator, get_ℓgrid, get_emulator_description\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Computes the CMB angular power spectrum for given cosmological parameters.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Arguments:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"input_params: Cosmological parameters as a vector (single evaluation) or matrix (batch evaluation)\nCℓemu::AbstractCℓEmulators: The emulator instance","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Returns:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Vector of Cℓ values on the emulator's ℓ-grid (single evaluation)\nMatrix of Cℓ values where each column is a spectrum (batch evaluation)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Input Validation:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Checks dimension compatibility with emulator\nValidates against NaN and Inf values\nSupports both 1D vectors and 2D matrices","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"# Single evaluation\nparams = [0.02237, 0.1200, 0.6736, 0.9649, 0.0544, 2.042e-9]\nCℓ = Capse.get_Cℓ(params, Cℓ_emu)\n\n# Batch evaluation\nparams_batch = rand(6, 100)  # 100 different cosmologies\nCℓ_batch = Capse.get_Cℓ(params_batch, Cℓ_emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#get_ℓgrid","page":"API Reference","title":"get_ℓgrid","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Capse.get_ℓgrid","page":"API Reference","title":"Capse.get_ℓgrid","text":"get_ℓgrid(CℓEmulator::AbstractCℓEmulators) -> AbstractVector\n\nReturn the multipole moments (ℓ values) on which the emulator was trained.\n\nArguments\n\nCℓEmulator::AbstractCℓEmulators: The emulator instance\n\nReturns\n\nAbstractVector: Array of ℓ values (typically ranges from 2 to ~2500)\n\nExample\n\nℓ_values = get_ℓgrid(emulator)\nprintln(\"ℓ range: \", first(ℓ_values), \" to \", last(ℓ_values))\nprintln(\"Number of multipoles: \", length(ℓ_values))\n\n# Find specific multipole\nℓ_target = 100\nidx = findfirst(==(ℓ_target), ℓ_values)\n\nSee also: get_Cℓ, CℓEmulator\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Returns the multipole moments (ℓ values) for which the power spectrum is computed.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Arguments:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"CℓEmulator::AbstractCℓEmulators: The emulator instance","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Returns:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"AbstractVector: Array of ℓ values","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"ℓ_values = Capse.get_ℓgrid(Cℓ_emu)\n# Typically returns something like [2, 3, 4, ..., 2500]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#get_emulator_description","page":"API Reference","title":"get_emulator_description","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#AbstractCosmologicalEmulators.get_emulator_description","page":"API Reference","title":"AbstractCosmologicalEmulators.get_emulator_description","text":"get_emulator_description(Cℓemu::AbstractCℓEmulators) -> Nothing\n\nDisplay detailed information about the emulator configuration.\n\nPrints to stdout:\n\nCosmological parameter names and ordering\nNetwork architecture details\nTraining configuration\nAccuracy metrics (if available)\nVersion information\n\nArguments\n\nCℓemu::AbstractCℓEmulators: The emulator instance\n\nReturns\n\nnothing (information is printed to stdout)\n\nExample\n\nget_emulator_description(emulator)\n# Output:\n# ===================================\n# Emulator Description\n# ===================================\n# Parameters: [ωb, ωc, h, ns, τ, As]\n# Architecture: 6 → 64 → 64 → 64 → 64 → 2500\n# Training samples: 100,000\n# Validation accuracy: 0.1%\n# ...\n\nwarning: Warning\nAlways check parameter ordering before using an emulator, as different training configurations may expect parameters in different orders.\n\nSee also: load_emulator, get_Cℓ\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Displays detailed information about the emulator configuration.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Arguments:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Cℓemu::AbstractCℓEmulators: The emulator instance","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Returns:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"nothing (prints to stdout)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Information Displayed:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Parameter names and ordering\nTraining configuration\nNetwork architecture details\nAccuracy metrics (if available)\nVersion information","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Capse.get_emulator_description(Cℓ_emu)\n# Output:\n# Emulator Description:\n# Parameters: [ωb, ωc, h, ns, σ8, As]\n# Architecture: 6 → 64 → 64 → 64 → 64 → 2500\n# Training samples: 100,000\n# ...","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#load_emulator","page":"API Reference","title":"load_emulator","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Capse.load_emulator","page":"API Reference","title":"Capse.load_emulator","text":"load_emulator(path::String; kwargs...) -> CℓEmulator\n\nLoad a pre-trained CMB power spectrum emulator from disk.\n\nArguments\n\npath::String: Directory path containing the emulator files (must end with '/')\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nemu::Type = SimpleChainsEmulator: Backend to use\nSimpleChainsEmulator: CPU-optimized (default)\nLuxEmulator: GPU-capable\nℓ_file::String = \"l.npy\": Filename for ℓ-grid\nweights_file::String = \"weights.npy\": Filename for network weights\ninminmax_file::String = \"inminmax.npy\": Filename for input normalization\noutminmax_file::String = \"outminmax.npy\": Filename for output normalization\nnn_setup_file::String = \"nn_setup.json\": Filename for network architecture\npostprocessing_file::String = \"postprocessing.jl\": Filename for post-processing function\n\nReturns\n\nCℓEmulator: Loaded emulator ready for inference\n\nRequired Files\n\nThe directory must contain:\n\nl.npy: Multipole grid\nweights.npy: Neural network weights\ninminmax.npy: Input normalization (2×n_params)\noutminmax.npy: Output normalization (2×n_ℓ)\nnn_setup.json: Architecture description\npostprocessing.jl: Post-processing function\n\nExamples\n\n# Basic loading\nemulator = load_emulator(\"/path/to/weights/\")\n\n# Use GPU backend\nusing Lux\nemulator = load_emulator(\"/path/to/weights/\", emu=LuxEmulator)\n\n# Custom filenames\nemulator = load_emulator(\n    \"/path/to/weights/\",\n    weights_file = \"model_weights.npy\",\n    ℓ_file = \"multipoles.npy\"\n)\n\n# Check what was loaded\nget_emulator_description(emulator)\n\nErrors\n\nSystemError: If path doesn't exist or files are missing\nLoadError: If files are corrupted or incompatible\n\ntip: Tip\nPre-trained emulators are available on Zenodo. Download and extract the weights folder, then load with this function.\n\nSee also: get_Cℓ, get_emulator_description, CℓEmulator\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Loads a pre-trained emulator from disk.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Arguments:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"path::String: Path to the directory containing emulator files","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Keyword Arguments:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"emu: Backend type (default: SimpleChainsEmulator)\nSimpleChainsEmulator: CPU-optimized backend\nLuxEmulator: GPU-capable backend\nℓ_file: Filename for ℓ-grid (default: \"l.npy\")\nweights_file: Filename for network weights (default: \"weights.npy\")\ninminmax_file: Filename for input normalization (default: \"inminmax.npy\")\noutminmax_file: Filename for output normalization (default: \"outminmax.npy\")\nnn_setup_file: Filename for network configuration (default: \"nn_setup.json\")\npostprocessing_file: Filename for post-processing function (default: \"postprocessing.jl\")","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Returns:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"CℓEmulator: Loaded emulator ready for inference","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Required Files: The specified directory must contain:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Neural network weights (.npy format)\nℓ-grid specification (.npy format)\nNormalization parameters (.npy format)\nNetwork architecture description (.json format)\nPost-processing function (.jl format)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"# Default loading\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"/path/to/weights/\")\n\n# Specify backend\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"/path/to/weights/\", emu=Capse.LuxEmulator)\n\n# Custom filenames\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\n    \"/path/to/weights/\",\n    weights_file = \"custom_weights.npy\",\n    ℓ_file = \"multipoles.npy\"\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Backend-Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Backend Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#SimpleChainsEmulator","page":"API Reference","title":"SimpleChainsEmulator","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"CPU-optimized backend using SimpleChains.jl. Best for:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Small to medium networks (< 1M parameters)\nSingle-threaded evaluation\nMaximum CPU performance\nLow latency requirements","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#LuxEmulator","page":"API Reference","title":"LuxEmulator","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Flexible backend using Lux.jl. Best for:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Large networks (> 1M parameters)\nGPU acceleration\nDistributed computing\nMixed precision computation","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Internal-Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Internal Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"These functions are used internally but may be useful for advanced users:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#maximin","page":"API Reference","title":"maximin","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Applies min-max normalization to inputs.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#inv_maximin","page":"API Reference","title":"inv_maximin","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Reverses min-max normalization on outputs.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#run_emulator","page":"API Reference","title":"run_emulator","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Executes the neural network forward pass.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Type-Hierarchy","page":"API Reference","title":"Type Hierarchy","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"AbstractCℓEmulators\n└── CℓEmulator\n\nAbstractTrainedEmulators\n├── SimpleChainsEmulator\n└── LuxEmulator","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Error-Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Error Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"The package may throw the following errors:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"ArgumentError: Invalid input dimensions or values\nAssertionError: Failed validation checks\nLoadError: Missing or corrupted emulator files\nMethodError: Incompatible backend or function calls","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Performance-Considerations","page":"API Reference","title":"Performance Considerations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Memory Layout: Column-major order for batch processing\nType Stability: Use consistent Float64 or Float32\nBackend Selection: SimpleChains for CPU, Lux for GPU\nBatch Size: Optimal batch size depends on hardware\nCPU: 10-100 samples\nGPU: 100-10,000 samples","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Thread-Safety","page":"API Reference","title":"Thread Safety","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"SimpleChainsEmulator: Thread-safe for read operations\nLuxEmulator: Use distributed computing for parallelism\nEmulator structs are immutable (as of v0.3.5)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#GPU-Support","page":"API Reference","title":"GPU Support","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"For GPU execution with Lux backend:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"using CUDA, Adapt\n\n# Load on CPU\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"weights/\", emu=Capse.LuxEmulator)\n\n# Move to GPU\nCℓ_emu_gpu = adapt(CuArray, Cℓ_emu)\n\n# Use normally\nparams_gpu = CuArray(params)\nCℓ_gpu = Capse.get_Cℓ(params_gpu, Cℓ_emu_gpu)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Extending-Capse.jl","page":"API Reference","title":"Extending Capse.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"To implement custom emulator backends:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Subtype AbstractTrainedEmulators\nImplement run_emulator method\nEnsure compatibility with normalization functions","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"struct MyCustomEmulator <: AbstractTrainedEmulators\n    # Your fields\nend\n\nfunction Capse.run_emulator(input, emu::MyCustomEmulator)\n    # Your implementation\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#Capse.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Capse.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: GitHub) (Image: arXiv) (Image: License)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Home","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Capse.jl is a high-performance Julia package for emulating Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB) Angular Power Spectra using neural networks. It provides speedups of 5-6 orders of magnitude compared to traditional Boltzmann codes like CAMB or CLASS, while maintaining high accuracy.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Key-Features","page":"Home","title":"Key Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"⚡ Ultra-fast inference: ~45 microseconds per evaluation\n🎯 High accuracy: Trained on high-precision cosmological simulations\n🔧 Multiple backends: Support for CPU (SimpleChains) and GPU (Lux) computation\n🐍 Python interoperability: Seamless integration via pycapse\n♻️ Auto-differentiable: Full support for gradient-based optimization\n🔬 Extensible: Built on AbstractCosmologicalEmulators.jl framework","category":"page"},{"location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","title":"Quick Start","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/CosmologicalEmulators/Capse.jl\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Basic-Usage","page":"Home","title":"Basic Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Capse\n\n# Load a trained emulator (download weights from Zenodo)\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"path/to/weights/\")\n\n# Define cosmological parameters\n# Order depends on training - check with get_emulator_description()\nparams = [0.02237, 0.1200, 0.6736, 0.9649, 0.0544, 2.042e-9]\n\n# Get CMB power spectrum\nCℓ = Capse.get_Cℓ(params, Cℓ_emu)\n\n# Access the ℓ-grid\nℓ_values = Capse.get_ℓgrid(Cℓ_emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Detailed-Guide","page":"Home","title":"Detailed Guide","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Loading-Emulators","page":"Home","title":"Loading Emulators","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Capse.jl supports loading pre-trained emulators from disk. Trained weights are available on Zenodo.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"# Default loading (uses SimpleChains backend)\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"path/to/weights/\")\n\n# Specify backend explicitly\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"path/to/weights/\", emu=Capse.SimpleChainsEmulator)\n\n# For GPU computation\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"path/to/weights/\", emu=Capse.LuxEmulator)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The weights folder should contain:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"weights.npy: Neural network weights\nl.npy: ℓ-grid for power spectrum\ninminmax.npy: Input normalization parameters\noutminmax.npy: Output normalization parameters\nnn_setup.json: Network architecture description\npostprocessing.jl: Post-processing function","category":"page"},{"location":"#Understanding-Parameters","page":"Home","title":"Understanding Parameters","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Each emulator is trained on specific cosmological parameters. To check the expected parameters:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"# Display emulator description including parameter ordering\nCapse.get_emulator_description(Cℓ_emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Common parameter sets include:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Standard ΛCDM: [ωb, ωc, h, ns, σ8, As]\nExtended models with neutrinos, dark energy, etc.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"⚠️ Important: Parameter ordering must match the training configuration exactly.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Batch-Processing","page":"Home","title":"Batch Processing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Process multiple parameter sets efficiently:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"# Create a matrix where each column is a parameter set\nparams_batch = rand(6, 100)  # 100 different cosmologies\n\n# Get all power spectra at once\nCℓ_batch = Capse.get_Cℓ(params_batch, Cℓ_emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Backend-Selection","page":"Home","title":"Backend Selection","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#SimpleChains-(CPU-optimized)","page":"Home","title":"SimpleChains (CPU-optimized)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Best for:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Small to medium neural networks\nSingle-threaded applications\nMaximum CPU performance","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using SimpleChains\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"weights/\", emu=Capse.SimpleChainsEmulator)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Lux-(GPU-capable)","page":"Home","title":"Lux (GPU-capable)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Best for:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Large neural networks\nGPU acceleration\nDistributed computing","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Lux, CUDA\nCℓ_emu = Capse.load_emulator(\"weights/\", emu=Capse.LuxEmulator)\n\n# Move to GPU\nusing Adapt\nCℓ_emu_gpu = adapt(CuArray, Cℓ_emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Error-Handling","page":"Home","title":"Error Handling","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Capse.jl includes robust input validation:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"# These will throw informative errors\ntry\n    # Wrong number of parameters\n    Capse.get_Cℓ(rand(5), Cℓ_emu)  # Expects 6 parameters\ncatch e\n    @error \"Parameter mismatch\" exception=e\nend\n\n# Check for invalid values\nparams = [0.02, 0.12, NaN, 0.96, 0.05, 2e-9]  # NaN will be caught","category":"page"},{"location":"#Performance","page":"Home","title":"Performance","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Benchmarks","page":"Home","title":"Benchmarks","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"On a 13th Gen Intel Core i7-13700H (single core):","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Method Time per evaluation Speedup\nCAMB (high accuracy) ~60 seconds 1×\nCLASS (high accuracy) ~50 seconds 0.8×\nCapse.jl (SimpleChains) ~45 μs ~1,300,000×\nCapse.jl (Lux) ~50 μs ~1,200,000×","category":"page"},{"location":"#Optimization-Tips","page":"Home","title":"Optimization Tips","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Use appropriate backend: SimpleChains for CPU, Lux for GPU\nBatch evaluations: Process multiple parameter sets together\nPre-allocate arrays: Reuse output arrays when possible\nType stability: Ensure consistent Float64/Float32 usage","category":"page"},{"location":"#Advanced-Usage","page":"Home","title":"Advanced Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Custom-Post-processing","page":"Home","title":"Custom Post-processing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Define custom post-processing functions:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"function custom_postprocessing(input, output, Cℓemu)\n    # Apply custom transformations\n    return output .* exp(input[1] - 3.0)\nend\n\nCℓ_emu = Capse.CℓEmulator(\n    TrainedEmulator = emu,\n    ℓgrid = ℓ_values,\n    InMinMax = input_norm,\n    OutMinMax = output_norm,\n    Postprocessing = custom_postprocessing\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Integration-with-Optimization","page":"Home","title":"Integration with Optimization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Use with gradient-based optimizers:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Zygote\n\nfunction loss(params)\n    Cℓ_theory = Capse.get_Cℓ(params, Cℓ_emu)\n    return sum((Cℓ_theory - Cℓ_observed).^2)\nend\n\n# Compute gradients\ngrad = gradient(loss, params)[1]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Uncertainty-Quantification","page":"Home","title":"Uncertainty Quantification","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"For emulators with uncertainty estimates:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"# Some emulators may provide uncertainty bands\nCℓ_mean, Cℓ_std = Capse.get_Cℓ_with_uncertainty(params, Cℓ_emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Python-Integration","page":"Home","title":"Python Integration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Use Capse.jl from Python via pycapse:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"import pycapse\n\n# Load emulator\nemu = pycapse.load_emulator(\"path/to/weights/\")\n\n# Evaluate\nimport numpy as np\nparams = np.array([0.02237, 0.1200, 0.6736, 0.9649, 0.0544, 2.042e-9])\ncl = pycapse.get_cl(params, emu)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Troubleshooting","page":"Home","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Common-Issues","page":"Home","title":"Common Issues","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Dimension mismatch error\nCheck parameter count matches emulator expectation\nVerify with get_emulator_description()\nPerformance issues with Lux in multi-threading\nKnown issue: Use distributed computing instead\nOr switch to SimpleChains for multi-threaded scenarios\nGPU out of memory\nReduce batch size\nUse mixed precision (Float32)\nLoading errors\nEnsure all required files are in weights folder\nCheck file permissions","category":"page"},{"location":"#Contributing","page":"Home","title":"Contributing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We welcome contributions! Please see our contribution guidelines.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Development-Setup","page":"Home","title":"Development Setup","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.develop(url=\"https://github.com/CosmologicalEmulators/Capse.jl\")\nPkg.test(\"Capse\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Citation","page":"Home","title":"Citation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you use Capse.jl in your research, please cite:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"@article{bonici2023capse,\n  title={Capse: efficient and auto-differentiable CMB power spectra emulation},\n  author={Bonici, M. and Bianchini, F. and Ruiz-Zapatero, J.},\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2307.14339},\n  year={2023}\n}","category":"page"},{"location":"#Authors","page":"Home","title":"Authors","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Marco Bonici - Postdoctoral Researcher, Waterloo Center for Astrophysics\nFederico Bianchini - Postdoctoral Researcher, Kavli Institute for Particle Physics and Cosmology\nJaime Ruiz-Zapatero - Research Software Engineer, Advanced Research Computing Centre, UCL\nMarius Millea - Researcher, UC Davis and Berkeley Center for Cosmological Physics","category":"page"},{"location":"#License","page":"Home","title":"License","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"MIT License - see LICENSE","category":"page"},{"location":"#Acknowledgments","page":"Home","title":"Acknowledgments","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This work builds upon AbstractCosmologicalEmulators.jl and benefits from the Julia ML ecosystem including SimpleChains.jl and Lux.jl.","category":"page"}]
